# env files (can opt-in for committing if needed)
.env*
.env.local

# vercel
.vercel

# typescript
*.tsbuildinfo
next-env.d.ts
.claudeignore
# PWA - auto-generated service worker files
/public/sw.js
/public/sw.js.map
/public/workbox-*.js
/public/workbox-*.js.map
/public/worker-*.js
/public/worker-*.js.map

.vercel

Perfect! ✅ Your backend is now fully updated to match the frontend slug format. Here's what was done:
                
  Backend Updates Summary                                                                               
                                                                          
  1. Product Endpoints Updated

  - Changed GET /api/products/:productId → GET /api/products/:slug
  - Now supports hierarchical slugs: /api/products/quran/gift-sets/product-name           
  - Update/Delete still use :id for MongoDB ObjectId
                                                                                                                      
  2. Slug Generator Utility Created (src/app/utils/generateSlug.ts)
                                                                                                                      
  - generateProductSlug(name, category) — Auto-generates hierarchical slugs                                         
  - Extracts colors/materials (royal-blue, wine, velvet, silk, resin, etc.)
  - Removes number suffixes (-1, -2)
  - Helper functions to extract category/subcategory from slugs

  3. Product Service Enhanced

  - Auto-generates slugs when creating products
  - Uses same pattern as frontend: category/subcategory/product-name-attributes
  - Backward compatible: fallback to ID lookup works

  4. Collections & Categories

  - Already using :slug format ✓
  - No changes needed

  API Examples

  Get Product by Slug:
  GET /api/products/quran/gift-sets/barkat-e-jariyah-quran-hamper-pastel-pink

  Create Product:
  POST /api/products
  {
    "name": "Barkat-e-Jariyah Quran Hamper",
    "category": "categoryId",
    // slug auto-generated!
  }

  Build Status: ✅ Success - No TypeScript errors

  Frontend and backend are now fully synchronized with the new slug format!

  